humanMachineDialogue.text: The N stage for cancer staging is determined by the number of lymph nodes involved. In this report, the patient has metastatic carcinoma in 22 of 33 lymph nodes, with extranodal extension and the largest metastasis being 1.4 cm. This indicates that the patient's N stage is N3, as per the AJCC Cancer Staging Manual, 7th Edition.
